d issue.{{citation needed|date=February 2020|reason=all information}}\n|-\n|colspan=4|'''''By an unknown mother'''''\n|-\n|Wilhelmine Alexandrine Pauline Alexandrov||1816||4 June 1863||Married ''Ivan Arduser von Hohendachs'', had issue.{{citation needed|date=February 2020|reason=all information}}\n|-\n|colspan=4|'''''By Veronica Dzierzanowska'''''\n|-\n|[[Gustaw Ehrenberg]]||14 February 1818||28 September 1895||Married firstly ''Felicite Pantcherow'', no issue. Married secondly, ''Emilie Pantcherow'', had one son.{{citation needed|date=February 2020|reason=all information}}\n|-\n|colspan=4|'''''By Barbara Tourkestanov, Princess Tourkestanova'''''\n|-\n|Maria Tourkestanova, ''Princess Tourkestanova''||20 March 1819||19 December 1843||Died aged twenty-four, no issue.{{citation needed|date=February 2020|reason=all information}}\n|-\n|colspan=4|'''''By Maria Ivanovna Katatcharova'''''\n|-\n|Nicolas Vassilievich Isakov||10 February 1821||25 February 1891||Married ''Anna Petrovna Lopukhina'' (a descendant of [[Eudoxia Lopukhina]]), had issue.{{citation needed|date=February 2020|reason=all information}}\n|}\n\n==Ancestry==\n{{ahnentafel\n|collapsed=yes |align=center\n| boxstyle_1 = background-color: #fcc;\n| boxstyle_2 = background-color: #fb9;\n| boxstyle_3 = background-color: #ffc;\n| boxstyle_4 = background-color: #bfc;\n| boxstyle_5 = background-color: #9fe;\n| 1 = 1. '''Alexander I of Russia'''\n| 2 = 2. [[Paul I of Russia]]{{citation needed|date=February 2020}}\n| 3 = 3. [[Maria Feodorovna (Sophie Dorothea of W\u00fcrttemberg)|Duchess Sophie Dorothea of W\u00fcrttemberg]]{{citation needed|date=February 2020}}\n| 4 = 4. [[Peter III of Russia]]{{sfn|Berlin|1768|p=22}}\n| 5 = 5. [[Catherine the Great|Catherine II of Russia]]{{sfn|Berlin|1768|p=22}}\n| 6 = 6. [[Frederick II Eugene, Duke of W\u00fcrttemberg]]{{sfn|Berlin|1768|p=21}}\n| 7 = 7. [[Princess Friederike of Brandenburg-Schwedt]]{{sfn|Berlin|1768|p=21}}\n| 8 = 8. [[Charles Frederick, Duke of Holstein-Gottorp]]{{s