port transferred to the [[Bloc Qu\u00e9b\u00e9cois]], which dominated this region for the better part of two decades; the Liberals only won Montmagny in 1997 and the [[Bonaventure\u2014\u00celes-de-la-Madeleine|Bonaventure]] region in 1993. When the BQ experienced a decline in 2000, the Liberals were able to win in the [[Gasp\u00e9sie\u2014\u00celes-de-la-Madeleine|Gasp\u00e9]], and took [[L\u00e9vis, Quebec|L\u00e9vis]] in a by-election. When the Liberals collapsed in Quebec, the Bloc regained all their lost seats in 2004. One of those seats, however was lost to the [[Conservative Party of Canada|Conservatives]] in 2006, and the Tories got another in a 2009.  Hopes of further Bloc gains were dashed in [[2011 Canadian federal election|2011]], as they were cut down to only one seat, with the NDP seizing one seat each from the Bloc and the Tories (the latter on a judicial recount).\n\n=== Votes by party throughout time ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Evolution of party standings throughout time\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\"|Party\n! colspan=\"2\"  scope=\"col\"|1993\n! colspan=\"2\"  scope=\"col\"|1997\n! colspan=\"2\"  scope=\"col\"|2000\n! colspan=\"2\"  scope=\"col\"|2004\n! colspan=\"2\"  scope=\"col\"|2006\n! colspan=\"2\"  scope=\"col\"|2008\n! colspan=\"2\"  scope=\"col\"|2011\n! colspan=\"2\"  scope=\"col\"|2015\n! colspan=\"2\"  scope=\"col\"|2019\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|Votes\n!scope=\"col\"|%\n!scope=\"col\"|Votes\n!scope=\"col\"|%\n!scope=\"col\"|Votes\n!scope=\"col\"|%\n!scope=\"col\"|Votes\n!scope=\"col\"|%\n!scope=\"col\"|Votes\n!scope=\"col\"|%\n!scope=\"col\"|Votes\n!scope=\"col\"|%\n!scope=\"col\"|Votes\n!scope=\"col\"|%\n!scope=\"col\"|Votes\n!scope=\"col\"|%\n!scope=\"col\"|Votes\n!scope=\"col\"|%\n|-\n| {{Canadian party colour|CA|Liberal|background}}|\n| |{{Canadian party colour|CA|Liberal|name}}\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"|72,292\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"|26.8%\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"|81,291\n| style=\"text-a